review_text: the cupboard is easy to install but can't take a lot of weight (eg. baby clothes plus 2 size 1 jumbo pack diapers) the metal bends as the weight is too much. The metal bars needs to be a stronger type of metal. I use it for my baby's clothes & meds instead of a chest of drawers as it's very compact. The material on each drawer could be a bit longer as the clothes falls down the back and down the sides. The cover should have Velcro straps on the inside to tie the cover against the metal bars so that the cupboard looks neat at all times and will also separate each drawer section as clothes won't fall down the back. Another 1-2 extra side pockets would have also been more beneficial. Lastly the stands that supports the cupboard should be a bit bigger & stronger to support a heavier weight as there is plenty of space. if there is too much clothes in or the weight of what's in it is too much then the cupboard leans to the side and does not stand upright anymore and the metal bar bends. I WOULD RECOMMEND THIS PRODUCT TO OTHERS SHOULD IT BE A BIT MORE STURDIER AS THIS IS AN AMAZING KIND OF CUPBOARD TO HAVE 🙂

review_text:
Exactly what I was looking for, for my office. Makes a surprisingly good filter coffee - Just a few notes to potential buyers:
1. Watch the water level the 1st time you use it - There is actually a MAX water mark inside, although barely visible, however, if you fill the travel cup almost full, it fills the resevoir to the mark.
2. As someone said in the reviews, use paper filters (I bought the AeroPress Micro Filters: 350 Sheets) and fits like a glove. Coffee brews a little longer, ensuring a great taste. 
3. Make sure not to add to much coffee your 1st try - I made a mess by adding too much coffee. For me 2 spoons works well, on one and a half cup of water.(350ml cup)

It is an overall great little machine and makes a decent cup of hot filter coffee if used with paper filters.

review_text:
Good screen, but maybe too much screen for me

The quality of the LG monitor is really solid—great resolution, nice colours, and everything looks good. No complaints there.

That said, I upgraded from a 27-inch to this 34-inch, and I’m not 100% convinced it was worth it. The extra screen space sounds great in theory, but in practice, I’m constantly shifting my eyes just to see everything. It feels like I’m always scanning left to right, and that can get a bit tiring.

With the 27-inch, things felt more focused. I could open what I needed and stay locked in without all the head movement. So while this monitor is definitely good, I’m just not sure the size upgrade fits how I work.

review_text: WoW!!!!! What a fantastic product!!! I have tried every product and home remedy under the sun.  Our 3 toilets were so badly stained and nothing worked till I got this product.  It does say do not use if you have a septic tank, which I do have.  So we stitched off the water supply, emptied all the water from the cistern and toilet bowl, poured in this chemical and used kitchen paper towels soaked in the chemical and stuck to the sides of the toilet.  We also used this product on our shower floors, wet some kitchen paper towels and blocked off the drain from the shower floor.  We left it for 2 hours and then use a scourer, and we now have brand new shower floors and toilets.  This was afterwards rinsed with clean water, water removed and then then switched on the water again.  Make sure you wears thick rubber gloves and a mask.  Thank you for an excellent products!

review_text:
I'm thoroughly impressed with the Arthur Ford Superior Perfume Navy Man #3!

As a perfume enthusiast, I'm always on the lookout for unique and captivating scents. This perfume exceeds my expectations!

Here's what I love about it:

- *Sophisticated Scent*: The fragrance is complex and alluring, with top notes that evoke a sense of freshness and confidence.
- *Long-Lasting*: The scent lingers on my skin for hours, making it perfect for everyday wear.
- *Unique Blend*: The combination of notes is unlike any other perfume I've tried, making it a standout in my collection.
- *Affordable Luxury*: The price is very reasonable, especially considering the high quality and concentration of the fragrance.
- *Elegant Packaging*: The bottle and packaging are sleek and sophisticated, making it a beautiful addition to my perfume collection.

Overall, I'm extremely satisfied with the Arthur Ford Superior Perfume Navy Man #3. It's a must-try for anyone looking for a distinctive and captivating fragrance!

Pros:
- Sophisticated scent
- Long-lasting
- Unique blend
- Affordable luxury
- Elegant packaging

Cons: None!
product_title: Arthur Ford Superior-Perfume Navy Man#3

The RAF Sandwich Toaster Machine is an absolute game-changer for quick and delicious meals! Its compact and sleek design makes it a perfect addition to any kitchen countertop. The non-stick surface ensures that your sandwiches come out perfectly toasted every time, without any sticking or mess. The handle stays cool, providing safe and comfortable handling, while the drip tray effectively catches any crumbs or grease, making cleanup a breeze.

What I love most about this toaster is its versatility. Whether you're in the mood for a classic grilled cheese, a hearty panini, or a quick breakfast toast, this machine delivers consistently excellent results. The even heating ensures that both sides of the bread are toasted to perfection, and the adjustable temperature settings allow you to customize your cooking to your liking.

Overall, the RAF Sandwich Toaster Machine is a must-have for anyone who loves a good sandwich. It's reliable, easy to use, and adds a touch of convenience to your daily routine. Highly recommended!

review_text:
Listen, if paper had a red carpet, Mondi Rotatrim would be front and center, striking a pose. I bought this box of A4 paper, and wow—who knew paper could be this premium?

The whiteness? Blinding. The smoothness? Like silk. This paper glides through my printer like it was born for the spotlight. No jams, no smudges, just crisp, professional-looking prints every time. It makes my documents look like they have their life together—even if I don’t!

Versatile & Reliable
Whether you’re printing work reports, school assignments, or your resignation letter (kidding… or am I?), this paper handles it all. Double-sided? No problem. The ink doesn’t bleed through, and the pages don’t curl up like they just heard bad news.

Great Value for Money
A whole box of 500 sheets? That’s like having a never-ending supply—unless you’re in an office where people print emails "just in case." But for personal use, this will last ages!

If you want premium, no-drama, smooth AF paper, Mondi Rotatrim is the one. Beyoncé said, “Flawless,” and she might’ve been talking about this paper. 10/10 would buy again!
product_title: Mondi Rotatrim Box of A4 Paper

review_text:
I recently added this drive to my home server, and it’s been an absolute game-changer. As someone who uses their server for a mix of personal projects, media storage, and occasional tinkering, I needed something fast, reliable, and efficient—and this SSD delivers on all fronts.

The first thing I noticed was the speed. With sequential read speeds of up to 3,500 MB/s and write speeds of up to 3,000 MB/s, my server feels snappier than ever. Whether I’m transferring large media files, running backups, or accessing my Plex library, everything happens in a flash. 

What really impressed me is how well it handles sustained workloads. I’ve had no issues with slowdowns, which is crucial for a home server that occasionally doubles as a testing ground for my projects.

Another big plus is the thermal performance. My server isn’t exactly a high-airflow setup, but the 980 stays cool even under load.  I don’t have to worry about overheating during extended use.

Installation was a breeze—I just slotted it into the M.2 slot on my server’s motherboard, and it was ready to go. 

I feel confident this drive will last for years to come. It’s also backed by Samsung’s solid reputation, which gives me extra peace of mind.
product_title: SAMSUNG 980 500 GB NVMe SSD

review_text:
Bought 2 of these units 4-5 months ago(One for me, one for the Wife). Saved me and my Wife both a tire on our cars each. One never charged (Solar has been enough to keep it charged) the other one (my unit) I have had to connect it to a USB cable so that it charges as soon as I get in the Bakkie to keep it working as Solar not enough to keep it charged up. With This I still recommend this to anyone as it does save you money as you can safe a tire before its to late (you can see when your tire pressure falls and can stop before it gets to low and damage the sidewall.) 
The unit itself is small and display is not the best but once you have the right angel that works for you, you will be very happy with it. The Valve caps are big! so if you want a clean look go for the inside the Tire units.
This unit is easy to install and easy to understand, Auto wakes when it picks up movement (By opening the door it sometimes wakes up already.)
Can adjust the max and min pressures warning.

review_text:
I’ve been using the HUAWEI MateBook D16 for a few weeks now, and I’m genuinely impressed. With 16GB of RAM and a massive 1TB SSD, this laptop handles everything I throw at it – from multitasking with heavy Excel sheets and Adobe apps to running virtual meetings and light gaming. The performance is incredibly smooth, and there’s virtually no lag, even with multiple tabs and programs open.
The 16-inch display is a game changer – it’s large, bright, and offers great clarity, especially for work and streaming. The slim bezels make it feel even more immersive. Despite its size, the MateBook D16 is surprisingly lightweight and portable, which is ideal for someone like me who’s often on the move.
Another standout is Huawei’s Super Device feature, which makes connecting and collaborating across my Huawei phone and tablet seamless. Transferring files or sharing screens is super intuitive. The keyboard is also very comfortable, with a numeric keypad included – a rare find these days.
Battery life is decent – I’m getting around 7 to 8 hours on average with mixed use, and the fast-charging via USB-C is a huge plus.
Overall, the MateBook D16 feels premium, performs like a beast, and delivers excellent value. If you're after a productivity powerhouse with serious storage and memory, this is a top contender.
product_title: Huawei MateBook D16 Intel Core i5-13420H 16GB RAM 1TB SSD 16"IPS FHD Laptop

review_text:
I bought the Omega Ergonomic Chair because my back was sending me break-up texts, and let me tell you, this chair is like the rebound relationship you never knew you needed. First off, the lumbar support? It's like a hug from your chiropractor, but without the small talk about your weekend plans. 

The adjustable armrests? They've got more positions than a yoga instructor at a flexibility convention. I've adjusted them so much, I might as well be training for the chair Olympics. And the seat? It's so cushioned, I've started questioning whether I'm sitting or floating in a zero-gravity chamber.

But here's the kicker - this chair is so comfortable, I've started doing my dishes from it. I mean, why stand when you can roll? I've even contemplated moving my entire life into this chair; bed, kitchen, office, all in one. I've considered renaming my home 'The Omega Throne Room'. 

One downside though - it's so comfy, I've fallen asleep mid-sentence during Zoom meetings. My boss now thinks I'm either meditating or in a coma. If you're looking to upgrade from your regular chair to something that feels like a luxury spaceship for your derrière, the Omega Ergonomic Chair is your ticket to a new life where standing is optional and productivity is questionable. 5 stars - or should I say, 5 lumbar supports?
product_title: Omega Ergonomic Chair

review_text:
This knitting machine has been such a fun tool to experiment with! If you’re into crafts, I’d definitely recommend it, but be prepared for a bit of trial and error. I’ve already made three beanies and even tried a sweater — although my stitches kept dropping.

I’d suggest getting weights for the legs or using a glass table so the suction cups stick well. If the machine isn’t stable, your stitches might drop, which can be frustrating. It seems to only do two types of stitches, and it doesn’t count rows in panel mode.

Yarn choice is also super important. Super fine yarn creates a strange, flimsy fabric, while thicker yarn can get stuck. But once you figure out the right materials, it’s incredibly convenient for fast projects. I also got all the extras, like darning needles, a crochet hook, and suction cups, which make the process easier.

Overall, despite the learning curve, I think it’s worth it if you love making things. It’s not perfect, but once you get used to it, the possibilities are endless.

UPDATE:
After a few weeks of use, I’ve noticed some wear and tear. The knob is starting to come loose and feels flimsy, and the wheel is scraping against the plastic housing, causing the white coating to peel off. I'm starting to worry about the machine's durability, especially with frequent use.
product_title: Hand Knitting Machine 48 Needles

review_text:
Cheap digital thermometers aren’t worth your kids health or life!

The quality of this device is backed by a 5 year warranty and it shows when you hold in your hand. 

It’s very accurate & has a high precision of repeatability. 

The backlight changes colour to indicate of high, low or normal body temperature. 

The backlight toggles on power up while warming up the nozzle (this improves accuracy). 

The digits displayed on the screen are large and easily read. 

The mini night light feature is perfect for night temperature reading on sick kids especially. No fumbling around. Just the right dimness & yellowish colour. 

NB: 
- The unit ships with batteries installed … YES 
- Always store the unit with one of the provided disposable caps on to avoid contamination on the IR sensor! ! !
- Replace the disposable caps when they almost finished

It’s not a fancy thermometer, it’s a priceless instrument. I highly recommend this unit over slightly cheaper digital units that can give erroneous misleading readings / info
product_title: Braun IRT6525 ThermoScan 7+ With Age Precision & Night Mode

But then when I went back to casting agencies, they refused to give me the role, saying my weight wasn’t right for the part. Then I realized sometimes it's not just the posture that's wrong. No matter how hard I try, some people will never be satisfied, and you can’t change that. So, here’s the thing, sometimes you just need to embrace your flaws. review_text:
Designed for both wet and dry use, this silicone massager aims to enhance scalp health by promoting circulation and effectively distributing shampoo.

Pros:

Gentle Silicone Bristles: The soft, flexible bristles provide a soothing massage without irritating the scalp, making it suitable for sensitive skin.

Ergonomic Design: The brush fits comfortably in hand, allowing for easy maneuverability during use.

Promotes Scalp Health: Regular use can help exfoliate the scalp, remove buildup, and potentially stimulate hair follicles, contributing to healthier hair growth.

Aesthetic Appeal: The baby pink color adds a touch of elegance to your shower essentials.

Cons:

Not Ideal for Fine Hair: Some users with fine or fragile hair have reported that the bristles can cause breakage if used with excessive force. It's recommended to use gentle, circular motions to avoid this issue.

Requires Proper Technique: To maximize benefits and prevent tangling, it's important to use the brush correctly—applying gentle pressure and avoiding aggressive movements.

Conclusion:
The Serina Beauty Shampoo Brush in Baby Pink offers a delightful blend of functionality and style. While it may not be suitable for all hair types, those with thicker or coarser hair will likely appreciate its benefits. Always ensure proper usage to enjoy a rejuvenating scalp massage experience.
product_title: Serina Beauty Shampoo Brush Hair Scalp Massagers Silicone Wet/Dry

review_text:
I bought this laptop because the description clearly stated that it comes with 512GB of storage, but when it arrived, I discovered it only had 256GB. That’s a huge difference and felt like false advertising. On top of that, after Windows system files, I was left with even less usable space.

Luckily, I had some extra money at the time and bought a 1TB external drive to fix the issue myself. But honestly, if I didn’t have the cash for that upgrade, I would’ve returned this laptop immediately.

The laptop itself works fine, but I can’t overlook being misled about a key spec like storage. If you’re planning to buy this model, double-check everything carefully—especially the actual specs vs. what’s advertised.

review_text: Won't blow your hair back if you're  looking for stand-alone maximum coverage. BUT once you learn how to use it, it's oh so very nice to have. Note that there are 2 shades. This shade is for olive and  brown skin tones. I noticed a lot of darker toned people had used the light pink perlescent shade and were surprised it didn't work for them. Yes, this product is not a game changer and does not have much coverage as a concealer, but there's a place for it. There is a mild sateen / shimmer effect that does actually reflect light and works well to make the under eye a little seem brighter. If you have no dark rings to hide or are going for a no makeup look or just need something to quickly refresh your under-eye mid-afternoon, then  this is your girl. You can also use it as a subtle daytime cheek highlighter that doesn't look too shimmery and clownish. I've had a few weeks to use it in different ways, such as over an under-eye concealer and as a suble cheek and chin highlight, and it's become a go-to quickie for a bit of a brighter look without too much effort. And I'm all about quick, easy to use items. So I'm back to get another in case they discontinue it.
